157
00:52:24,700 --> 00:52:26,100
[UNKNOWN] Thank you.

158
00:53:00,480 --> 00:53:05,200
[SPEAKER_14] Honorable Assembly, I now call upon Ágnes Forsthofer, who will say a few words.

159
00:53:20,220 --> 00:53:25,820
[SPEAKER_13] Honorable National Assembly, esteemed colleagues, esteemed fellow citizens!

160
00:53:26,460 --> 00:53:30,320
[SPEAKER_13] I am deeply honored to address you today, in gratitude for your trust.

161
00:53:31,360 --> 00:53:36,140
[SPEAKER_13] I know precisely and understand exactly what responsibility the trust placed in me entails.

162
00:53:37,180 --> 00:53:42,080
[SPEAKER_13] I know precisely that with this trust, I have not received power, but a service.

163
00:53:42,080 --> 00:53:48,060
[SPEAKER_13] From my faith as well, I know that from those to whom much has been entrusted, much will be demanded.

164
00:53:48,740 --> 00:53:54,700
[SPEAKER_13] Today is not a day for me, but for the Hungarian nation, opening a historical opportunity.

165
00:53:56,080 --> 00:54:01,820
[SPEAKER_13] Changes are coming that will mark the beginning of a new era in the history of Hungarian parliamentary democracy.

166
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:10,020
[SPEAKER_13] For the National Assembly must once again be the home of the Hungarian nation, the house of Hungary, not the parties.

167
00:54:10,020 --> 00:54:15,260
[UNKNOWN] It must not be a center of power, but a sanctuary of the will of the nation.

168
00:54:16,080 --> 00:54:26,380
[SPEAKER_13] This house will once again be the house of humility and modesty, of service and the desire to act, not the level of lordliness, grandstanding, or self-display.

169
00:54:27,360 --> 00:54:33,520
[SPEAKER_13] Where we are not better or worse than one another, but rather balance each other.

170
00:54:34,740 --> 00:54:38,520
[SPEAKER_13] In every statement, we must strive for the unity of the Hungarian nation.

171
00:54:38,520 --> 00:54:49,080
[SPEAKER_13] Let there be room here for argumentation, persuasion, understanding, respectful dialogue based on facts, and even for apologies.

172
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:52,340
[SPEAKER_13] And let there be room for love.

173
00:54:53,300 --> 00:55:04,040
[SPEAKER_13] The first Hungarian female parliamentarian, Margit Slachta, stands before me as an example with her courageous stance, social sensitivity, and Christian commitment.

174
00:55:04,220 --> 00:55:06,040
[SPEAKER_13] I quote her words.

175
00:55:06,860 --> 00:55:12,300
[SPEAKER_13] Without love, a community has no life, no growth, and no success.

176
00:55:12,900 --> 00:55:18,960
[SPEAKER_13] We will love our homeland in this house, we will love the Hungarian people.

177
00:55:20,040 --> 00:55:28,940
[SPEAKER_13] And we will show this by creating laws that serve the honor and rise of the Hungarian nation with responsibility and integrity.

178
00:55:30,040 --> 00:55:35,160
[SPEAKER_13] We will work so that no one is stigmatized, a second-class citizen,

179
00:55:36,040 --> 00:55:38,300
[SPEAKER_13] because of their political opinion, lifestyle, or mode of work at the national assembly.

180
00:55:39,200 --> 00:55:48,200
[SPEAKER_13] Let our country and our parliament once again belong to everyone who lives here, who works here, or whom the heart draws back from the wider world.

181
00:55:49,160 --> 00:55:55,420
[SPEAKER_13] Let the voice of everyone reach these walls who entrusted us with their mandate through representation.

182
00:55:56,280 --> 00:56:00,200
[SPEAKER_13] Let the work of the National Assembly be transparent and open.

183
00:56:00,560 --> 00:56:03,080
[SPEAKER_13] Let it be more open toward the free press.

184
00:56:03,080 --> 00:56:07,440
[SPEAKER_13] Let it be more understandable to civil society, and especially to the youth.

185
00:56:08,460 --> 00:56:12,400
[SPEAKER_13] Let those who are interested clearly see and hear how we work for them.

186
00:56:13,120 --> 00:56:20,180
[SPEAKER_13] Let them see that the world is diverse, and so is meaningful debate, but it is based on mutual respect.

187
00:56:21,080 --> 00:56:30,000
[SPEAKER_13] Therefore, I ask my fellow representatives to transcend political opinions and jointly restore the image of the National Assembly.

188
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:35,280
[SPEAKER_13] Because the restoration of public trust begins here, in the parliament.

189
00:56:35,800 --> 00:56:40,820
[SPEAKER_13] Let the work of the National Assembly be worthy of the mandate we received from the Hungarian people.

190
00:56:41,540 --> 00:56:52,380
[SPEAKER_13] We do not serve the citizens of Hungary adequately when we are loud, but when, by understanding each other better, we are able to build bridges even over the chasms.

191
00:56:53,080 --> 00:56:57,480
[SPEAKER_13] A new mindset is also needed in the leadership of the National Assembly office.

192
00:56:57,480 --> 00:57:04,440
[SPEAKER_13] The maintenance of order must not serve as an excuse for limiting political opinions and retreating into isolation.

193
00:57:05,480 --> 00:57:12,420
[SPEAKER_13] Value creation will not be manifested in measures and appearances that waste public funds and display power,

194
00:57:13,480 --> 00:57:20,040
[SPEAKER_13] but in the new opportunities created through responsible management and in committed legislative work.

195
00:57:20,560 --> 00:57:27,460
[SPEAKER_13] If we work this way, then according to the plan of Saint Stephen, our path will once again lead back to Europe.

196
00:57:27,480 --> 00:57:34,380
[SPEAKER_13] Let the first symbolic step on this path be my first decision as Speaker.

197
00:57:35,260 --> 00:57:44,140
[SPEAKER_13] I order that today, after 12 years, the flag of the European Union be returned to the building of the Hungarian parliament.

198
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:03,940
[UNKNOWN] Thank you very much!

199
00:58:03,940 --> 00:58:13,900
[SPEAKER_13] This flag is the symbol of the alliance to which Hungarian voters gave an overwhelming majority in favor 22 years ago.

200
00:58:14,320 --> 00:58:19,140
[SPEAKER_13] Belonging to this alliance remains today an elemental interest of the Hungarian nation.

201
00:58:20,220 --> 00:58:27,460
[SPEAKER_13] Follow this first symbolic step with many others, through which we will once again become respected members of European communities.

202
00:58:28,740 --> 00:58:34,160
[UNKNOWN] Expressing my gratitude once again, I now face this honorable task.

203
00:58:34,200 --> 00:58:41,660
