01:53:18,200 --> 01:53:29,040
[SPEAKER_01] they built two tunnels, each about 45 to 50 meters long, beneath the square. We know that if you put something underground, like a cellar, we go down into the cellar, and it's cold there.

847
01:53:29,040 --> 01:53:37,240
[SPEAKER_01] They actually made use of the fact that in these tunnels, they let in the outside air from above through fountains.

848
01:53:37,280 --> 01:53:42,900
[SPEAKER_01] The fountain was good not only for cooling the air but also for filtering it from dust and soot.

849
01:53:43,240 --> 01:53:50,360
[SPEAKER_01] In these tunnels, they sucked in this air, and they were actually able to produce a cool, low-temperature air of about ten degrees,

850
01:53:50,360 --> 01:53:59,800
[SPEAKER_01] and with the help of various fans and suitable spaces, they could bring this cold air under the assembly rooms.

851
01:53:59,820 --> 01:54:08,100
[SPEAKER_01] However, the system didn't work entirely like that, because the precise temperature, the relatively precise temperature, didn't function like a modern thermostat,

852
01:54:08,160 --> 01:54:12,560
[SPEAKER_01] where you can set it to a tenth of a degree, for example, to specify the desired temperature.

853
01:54:12,680 --> 01:54:18,160
[SPEAKER_01] By appropriately mixing the warm air coming from the boiler room,

854
01:54:19,220 --> 01:54:24,040
[SPEAKER_01] they could practically set a fairly specific temperature, and this air reached the assembly rooms,

855
01:54:24,100 --> 01:54:30,180
[SPEAKER_01] and simply by the gravity of the cold and warm air, it reached the deputies below.

856
01:54:30,220 --> 01:54:39,620
[SPEAKER_01] By the way, under each chair there is a small grid, and through that, this pre-set cold, cool, or even warm air would rise.

857
01:54:39,740 --> 01:54:45,980
[SPEAKER_01] And the extraction of this air was handled from above, the chandeliers were suitable for this, these are open structures,

858
01:54:45,980 --> 01:54:53,440
[SPEAKER_01] through which they sucked in the air from the space, and thus created a kind of air current in which it was pleasant to work.

859
01:54:54,020 --> 01:54:57,680
[SPEAKER_11] Despite the need to address and resolve these issues.

860
01:54:57,860 --> 01:55:06,580
