1309
02:46:56,550 --> 02:47:02,770
[UNKNOWN] Honorable fellow citizens, Hungarians, both within and beyond the borders,

1310
02:47:03,930 --> 02:47:07,210
[UNKNOWN] honored guests, honored colleagues!

1311
02:47:07,210 --> 02:47:13,830
[UNKNOWN] In this festive moment, I stand before you with emotion.

1312
02:47:14,270 --> 02:47:24,370
[SPEAKER_16] I have just sworn an oath to serve our wonderful country, Hungary, to serve a nation

1313
02:47:24,430 --> 02:47:31,430
[UNKNOWN] whose first Prime Minister was Count Lajos Batthyány, who was deposed at Martonvásár.

1314
02:47:32,470 --> 02:47:34,690
[SPEAKER_16] Just as 36 years ago,

1315
02:47:34,690 --> 02:47:37,470
[SPEAKER_16] in 1990,

1316
02:47:37,590 --> 02:47:42,530
[SPEAKER_16] in these very halls, the late Prime Minister József Antall recalled

1317
02:47:42,710 --> 02:47:46,930
[SPEAKER_16] the fate of Count Lajos Batthyány and Pál Teleki,

1318
02:47:47,090 --> 02:47:52,490
[SPEAKER_16] and later, Prime Minister Imre Nagy's martyr's death for the nation,

1319
02:47:52,590 --> 02:47:57,050
[SPEAKER_16] serves as a warning for every Prime Minister of Hungary,

1320
02:47:57,110 --> 02:48:01,190
[SPEAKER_16] and is an eternal symbol of Hungarian history.

1321
02:48:01,930 --> 02:48:04,590
[SPEAKER_16] Therefore, our predecessors gave their lives for the nation,

1322
02:48:04,690 --> 02:48:06,450
[SPEAKER_16] sacrificing their lives.

1323
02:48:07,690 --> 02:48:15,850
[SPEAKER_16] Being the Prime Minister of Hungary carries a great political and human responsibility.

1324
02:48:16,050 --> 02:48:18,890
[SPEAKER_16] But it also carries a historical burden,

1325
02:48:19,070 --> 02:48:25,230
[UNKNOWN] that their sacrifice, the sacrifice of millions, made for the nation,

1326
02:48:25,230 --> 02:48:29,610
[UNKNOWN] must not, cannot be in vain.

1327
02:48:30,110 --> 02:48:33,630
[UNKNOWN] With faith, with willpower,

1328
02:48:35,090 --> 02:48:39,130
[SPEAKER_16] with love for the homeland, I will work every day of the year,

1329
02:48:39,130 --> 02:48:41,770
[SPEAKER_16] every hour of the day, in order

1330
02:48:42,630 --> 02:48:46,670
[SPEAKER_16] to live up to the warning example set by predecessors such as

1331
02:48:46,670 --> 02:48:51,410
[SPEAKER_16] Lajos Battyányi, Imre Nagy, or even József Antall.

1332
02:48:53,590 --> 02:48:57,330
[SPEAKER_16] Integrity, courage, wisdom.

1333
02:48:59,090 --> 02:49:03,610
[SPEAKER_16] As Prime Minister, with due humility, I will take example from them,

1334
02:49:03,610 --> 02:49:06,010
[SPEAKER_16] and learn from them.

1335
02:49:07,290 --> 02:49:10,490
[SPEAKER_16] I feel and understand my responsibility.

1336
02:49:11,710 --> 02:49:14,130
[SPEAKER_16] I have seen the fate of my predecessors,

1337
02:49:14,230 --> 02:49:16,690
[UNKNOWN] and not only that of the heroes.

1338
02:49:17,510 --> 02:49:22,310
[SPEAKER_16] I have also seen how the position of Prime Minister

1339
02:49:22,310 --> 02:49:27,310
[SPEAKER_16] can be placed in the service of power instead of the service of the nation.

1340
02:49:28,310 --> 02:49:33,590
[SPEAKER_16] I have seen how power can slowly crush people beneath it.

1341
02:49:33,590 --> 02:49:40,590
[SPEAKER_16] how a politician can gradually become a prisoner of their own system,

1342
02:49:40,730 --> 02:49:47,690
[SPEAKER_16] and how a political community can lose its connection with the people

1343
02:49:47,830 --> 02:49:51,050
[SPEAKER_16] from whom it originally received its mandate.

1344
02:49:51,790 --> 02:49:58,110
[SPEAKER_16] Hungarian history is a warning for every prime minister.

1345
02:49:59,670 --> 02:50:02,510
[SPEAKER_16] A warning that power is transient.

1346
02:50:02,510 --> 02:50:09,150
[SPEAKER_16] However, the consequences of our decisions remain with us for generations.

1347
02:50:09,750 --> 02:50:14,810
[SPEAKER_16] A country can be lifted up by a few brave and honest decisions,

1348
02:50:15,010 --> 02:50:23,610
[UNKNOWN] but it can also be destroyed by selfishness, arrogance, short-sightedness, or even mediocrity.

1349
02:50:24,390 --> 02:50:32,370
[SPEAKER_16] That is why I would like to clearly state here, in the house of Hungarian democracy and constitutionalism,

1350
02:50:32,370 --> 02:50:38,490
[SPEAKER_16] that I will not rule Hungary, I will serve my country.

1351
02:50:39,170 --> 02:50:47,670
[SPEAKER_16] The words of József Antall set the moral standard and duty for this service for us.

1352
02:50:47,910 --> 02:50:52,230
[SPEAKER_16] I will serve as long as my service is useful.

1353
02:50:52,510 --> 02:50:59,410
[UNKNOWN] I do this to the best of my knowledge, as long as I can and as long as the Hungarian nation demands it.

1354
02:50:59,410 --> 02:51:07,290
[UNKNOWN] I am not standing here because I am somehow special or superior to anyone else in the country. I am not.

1355
02:51:07,750 --> 02:51:16,210
[UNKNOWN] I am standing here because millions of Hungarians have decided they want change.

1356
02:51:16,390 --> 02:51:26,310
[SPEAKER_16] And this trust we have received is both an honor, a serious moral responsibility, and a wonderful feeling.

1357
02:51:26,310 --> 02:51:32,510
[SPEAKER_16] A wonderful feeling, because working for this country is uplifting.

1358
02:51:32,910 --> 02:51:46,370
[SPEAKER_16] There is no other place in the world where so much talent, so much perseverance, so much pain, and so much will to live have converged in the history of a single nation.

1359
02:51:47,190 --> 02:51:52,950
[SPEAKER_16] Hungary is wonderful because it has repeatedly been able to rise again.

1360
02:51:53,470 --> 02:51:56,290
[SPEAKER_16] Even when many had already given up on it.

1361
02:51:56,310 --> 02:52:11,730
[SPEAKER_16] Because in this country, millions of people work quietly and with dignity, day after day, for their families, their communities, and their beloved homeland.

1362
02:52:12,850 --> 02:52:21,970
[SPEAKER_16] Hungary is our homeland, which can be heartbreakingly sad and at the same time infinitely joyful.

1363
02:52:22,110 --> 02:52:25,390
[SPEAKER_16] Our homeland is full of hardship.

1364
02:52:25,390 --> 02:52:33,990
[SPEAKER_16] Joy, humor, ingenuity, yearning for freedom, and love of country.

1365
02:52:34,430 --> 02:52:41,350
[SPEAKER_16] Our homeland, our fate, the future of our children and grandchildren.

1366
02:52:43,390 --> 02:52:53,890
[SPEAKER_16] Fellow countrymen, in the history of the Third Hungarian Republic, the strength with which the Hungarian people have stood on the side of change is unprecedented.

1367
02:52:53,890 --> 02:52:57,130
[SPEAKER_16] On April 12, 2026.

1368
02:52:57,970 --> 02:53:09,070
[SPEAKER_16] The number of people who participated in the parliamentary election was unprecedented, just as the 3,385,000 votes for change were.

1369
02:53:09,750 --> 02:53:17,990
[SPEAKER_16] Unprecedented is the path that Hungary, the Hungarian people, have taken in the past two years.

1370
02:53:18,650 --> 02:53:20,010
[SPEAKER_16] I thank them!

1371
02:53:21,310 --> 02:53:22,350
[SPEAKER_16] I thank them!

1372
02:53:22,350 --> 02:53:38,930
[SPEAKER_16] Thank you to everyone present within the walls of the National Assembly, or as its designer Imre Steindl called it, the temple of the constitution, for hearing and understanding this will.

1373
02:53:39,450 --> 02:53:47,370
[UNKNOWN] The Hungarian people have given us the mandate to end decades of drifting.

1374
02:53:47,730 --> 02:53:52,330
[SPEAKER_16] They have given us the mandate to open a new chapter.

1375
02:53:52,330 --> 02:53:59,490
[SPEAKER_16] Do you know that we are to change not only the government, but the system?

1376
02:53:59,830 --> 02:54:01,710
[UNKNOWN] To start anew.

1377
02:54:03,330 --> 02:54:09,750
[SPEAKER_16] We must know, however, that there is no starting anew without reconciliation.

1378
02:54:10,450 --> 02:54:14,630
[SPEAKER_16] Reconciliation, however, is not possible without justice.

1379
02:54:15,870 --> 02:54:19,570
[SPEAKER_16] Justice, in turn, is not possible without facing the truth.

1380
02:54:22,130 --> 02:54:27,990
[SPEAKER_16] We need to face the truth, seek justice, achieve reconciliation, and start anew.

1381
02:54:28,250 --> 02:54:36,890
[SPEAKER_16] If any of these elements are missing for the Hungarian people who have entrusted us with authority, they must be disappointed once again.

1382
02:54:37,790 --> 02:54:39,930
[SPEAKER_16] Honorable colleagues!

1383
02:54:41,410 --> 02:54:43,070
[SPEAKER_16] We need to face the facts.

1384
02:54:44,750 --> 02:54:45,750
[SPEAKER_16] Symbolically.

1385
02:54:45,750 --> 02:54:53,830
[SPEAKER_16] because the two prime ministers who gave their names to the Orbán-Gyurcsány era are not sitting here today in the rows of benches,

1386
02:54:53,990 --> 02:55:00,410
[SPEAKER_16] to openly and clearly speak about the legacy they have left behind.

1387
02:55:01,190 --> 02:55:05,670
[SPEAKER_16] Not simply because their parties lost the election,

1388
02:55:05,810 --> 02:55:12,510
[SPEAKER_16] but because they failed politically, personally, and morally.

1389
02:55:13,090 --> 02:55:15,730
[SPEAKER_16] The political system failed,

1390
02:55:15,750 --> 02:55:19,290
[SPEAKER_16] which constantly fed off each other,

1391
02:55:19,450 --> 02:55:21,690
[SPEAKER_16] even looted the country,

1392
02:55:21,830 --> 02:55:24,810
[SPEAKER_16] mobilized people against one another,

1393
02:55:24,970 --> 02:55:32,730
[SPEAKER_16] while depleting Hungary’s economic, moral, and social reserves.

1394
02:55:33,790 --> 02:55:43,010
[SPEAKER_16] Twenty-two years after Hungary received the greatest opportunity in its modern history through EU accession,

1395
02:55:43,010 --> 02:55:47,510
[SPEAKER_16] our beloved homeland has already become a scorched earth.

1396
02:55:48,210 --> 02:55:55,330
[UNKNOWN] It was looted, plundered, betrayed, and misled.

1397
02:55:56,050 --> 02:56:00,270
[SPEAKER_16] And when they should take responsibility for all this,

1398
02:56:01,010 --> 02:56:11,130
[SPEAKER_16] they run away from their own political community and the country, resign,

1399
02:56:13,010 --> 02:56:16,330
[UNKNOWN] withdraw, and wash their hands.

1400
02:56:17,110 --> 02:56:24,590
[UNKNOWN] The fact that they are not sitting here today is a precise reflection of this political culture.

1401
02:56:24,690 --> 02:56:29,150
[SPEAKER_16] which has ruled this country for decades,

1402
02:56:30,130 --> 02:56:35,990
[UNKNOWN] of responsibility avoidance, the complete lack of self-examination

1403
02:56:35,990 --> 02:56:39,930
[SPEAKER_16] and power exercised without consequences.

1404
02:56:39,930 --> 02:56:45,770
[SPEAKER_16] But the Hungarian people, dear colleagues,

1405
02:56:45,850 --> 02:56:54,170
[SPEAKER_16] will not do the favor of allowing this confrontation to be avoided.

1406
02:56:54,810 --> 02:57:01,570
[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a country where three million people live in poverty,

1407
02:57:01,830 --> 02:57:06,170
[SPEAKER_16] 800,000 pensioners below the minimum subsistence level,

1408
02:57:06,170 --> 02:57:14,630
[SPEAKER_16] 400,000 children growing up in deprivation and social exclusion.

1409
02:57:14,970 --> 02:57:22,890
[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a country where the outgoing government managed to accumulate

1410
02:57:22,890 --> 02:57:28,770
[SPEAKER_16] more than 90 percent of the annual planned budget deficit in just three months.

1411
02:57:29,210 --> 02:57:35,550
[SPEAKER_16] Where power failed, and the failed power, even in its final hours,

1412
02:57:37,750 --> 02:57:41,930
[SPEAKER_16] tried to steal everything that was movable.

1413
02:57:42,350 --> 02:57:49,390
[UNKNOWN] We inherited a country where tens of thousands of people die prematurely every year because

1414
02:57:49,470 --> 02:57:53,530
[SPEAKER_16] the healthcare system was bled dry.

1415
02:57:54,090 --> 02:57:58,070
[SPEAKER_16] Where 900,000 people do not have their own family doctor.

1416
02:57:58,770 --> 02:58:04,470
[SPEAKER_16] Where one has to wait weeks or years for an examination or a surgery,

1417
02:58:04,470 --> 02:58:10,810
[SPEAKER_16] and where people live five years less than the European average.

1418
02:58:11,510 --> 02:58:17,450
[UNKNOWN] We inherited a country where education has become, not a means of upward mobility,

1419
02:58:17,450 --> 02:58:23,070
[SPEAKER_16] but increasingly a tool for the reproduction of social inequalities.

1420
02:58:23,950 --> 02:58:32,870
[SPEAKER_16] Where a child's fate is often already determined at the moment of birth by the family's financial situation and place of residence.

1421
02:58:34,470 --> 02:58:43,450
[UNKNOWN] We inherited a country where half of adult Hungarians try to live on less than 300,000 forints,

1422
02:58:44,470 --> 02:58:50,410
[SPEAKER_16] while prices have spiraled out of control and our money has lost nearly half its value,

1423
02:58:51,470 --> 02:58:58,050
[SPEAKER_16] and housing has become an unattainable luxury for hundreds of thousands of young families.

1424
02:58:59,470 --> 02:59:04,450
[UNKNOWN] We inherited a country where child protection left many people,

1425
02:59:04,450 --> 02:59:09,970
[UNKNOWN] often leaving the most vulnerable children completely alone,

1426
02:59:10,170 --> 02:59:21,610
[SPEAKER_16] and where countless young people had to grow up, or still have to grow up, in fear, humiliation, or without love,

1427
02:59:22,450 --> 02:59:29,150
[SPEAKER_16] in institutions that were supposed to provide them with safety.

1428
02:59:29,590 --> 02:59:32,630
[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a country,

1429
02:59:32,630 --> 02:59:47,250
[SPEAKER_16] where the state promoted the enrichment of a narrow political and economic elite instead of its own citizens, while trillions,

1430
02:59:47,350 --> 03:00:02,610
[SPEAKER_16] Trillions disappeared from foundations, from the National Bank, through overpriced and unnecessary investments and political,

1431
03:00:02,610 --> 03:00:04,070
[SPEAKER_16] into the pockets of various client groups in Hungary.

1432
03:00:04,230 --> 03:00:12,550
[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a Hungary that has become the most corrupt member state of the European Union,

1433
03:00:12,790 --> 03:00:18,030
[SPEAKER_16] and where the wealth siphoned off, stolen from the common service of the Hungarian nation over the past one and a half decades is estimated at 20,000 billion forints,

1434
03:00:18,190 --> 03:00:28,310
[SPEAKER_16] from the pockets of the Hungarian people.

1435
03:00:28,350 --> 03:00:30,790
[SPEAKER_16] From the pockets of the Hungarian people.

1436
03:00:31,090 --> 03:00:32,590
[UNKNOWN] From the pockets of the Hungarian people.

1437
03:00:32,590 --> 03:00:36,490
[SPEAKER_16] From the tables of Hungarian children and the elderly.

1438
03:00:36,490 --> 03:00:50,250
[SPEAKER_16] A country where 8,000 billion forints in EU funds became inaccessible due to corruption and the deliberate dismantling of the rule of law.

1439
03:00:50,430 --> 03:01:02,210
[SPEAKER_16] This is the money of the Hungarian people, from which hospitals, schools, roads, and businesses could have developed.

1440
03:01:02,230 --> 03:01:02,570
[SPEAKER_16] This is the money of the Hungarian people, from which hospitals, schools, roads, and businesses could have developed.

1441
03:01:02,590 --> 03:01:04,090
[UNKNOWN] This is the money of the Hungarian people, from which hospitals, schools, roads, and businesses could have developed.

1442
03:01:04,090 --> 03:01:11,350
[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a country where politics deliberately turned Hungarians against Hungarians.

1443
