[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a country where politics deliberately turned Hungarians against Hungarians.

1444
03:01:21,630 --> 03:01:26,090
[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a country where politics deliberately turned Hungarians against Hungarians.

1445
03:01:26,730 --> 03:01:32,570
[SPEAKER_16] We inherited a country where politics deliberately turned Hungarians against Hungarians.

1446
03:01:32,570 --> 03:01:42,530
[SPEAKER_16] they lost their faith in the idea that this country could still be a fair, humane, and shared homeland for all Hungarians.

1447
03:01:44,110 --> 03:01:56,830
[SPEAKER_16] Fellow citizens, for the politics of the past two decades, with the exception of a narrow power elite, the entire country paid a heavy price.

1448
03:01:56,830 --> 03:02:13,210
[SPEAKER_16] Our emotionally Fidesz-aligned compatriots, the voters of our homeland, the left-wing voters, and even those who, disillusioned, turned their backs on politics—also paid a price.

1449
03:02:14,690 --> 03:02:19,770
[SPEAKER_16] Let us state clearly: what happened was not the fault of the Hungarian people.

1450
03:02:20,210 --> 03:02:25,870
[SPEAKER_16] The Hungarian people have just proven that, in contrast to their leaders,

1451
03:02:26,830 --> 03:02:41,090
[UNKNOWN] this country is capable of renewal, capable of reason, capable of expressing the desire and demand for freedom and justice.

1452
03:02:41,230 --> 03:02:56,190
[SPEAKER_16] The Hungarian nation, often described and blamed by scientists, journalists, and opinion-makers, is far wiser, far more democratic.

1453
03:02:56,830 --> 03:03:07,270
[SPEAKER_16] Far more patriotic than its own political elite, which has betrayed it over the past decades.

1454
03:03:07,950 --> 03:03:14,670
[SPEAKER_16] While the right and left-wing politics kept each other in check, they also sustained one another.

1455
03:03:15,130 --> 03:03:26,810
[SPEAKER_16] While continuously mobilizing their own factions against each other, in reality, they mutually maintained each other's political system.

1456
03:03:26,830 --> 03:03:33,990
[SPEAKER_16] Every political side must confront its own responsibility.

1457
03:03:34,230 --> 03:03:46,550
[SPEAKER_16] Former ruling party representatives and the Fidesz power elite will have a long way to go toward this confrontation.

1458
03:03:46,850 --> 03:03:55,830
[SPEAKER_16] This confrontation will only take its first step when it is acknowledged that their leaders caused

1459
03:03:56,210 --> 03:04:01,010
[SPEAKER_16] such damage, both personally and in a moral sense.

1460
03:04:01,250 --> 03:04:17,310
[SPEAKER_16] The true confrontation will come when the question can also be raised: how the civic right wing, the former civic right wing, allowed this damage to occur.

1461
03:04:17,590 --> 03:04:25,290
[SPEAKER_16] that former opposition, which has fallen out of the National Assembly, also has to account for the fact

1462
03:04:25,290 --> 03:04:32,270
[SPEAKER_16] that it often considered its own political survival more important than the future of the country.

1463
03:04:32,410 --> 03:04:43,550
[SPEAKER_16] Democracy was not dismantled by the former opposition, but for many years it was content with an opposition role without consequences,

1464
03:04:43,690 --> 03:04:48,730
[SPEAKER_16] while our country drifted deeper and deeper into an ever more serious crisis.

1465
03:04:49,150 --> 03:04:53,130
[SPEAKER_16] The Hungarian people do not deserve such an elite.

1466
03:04:53,130 --> 03:05:01,410
[UNKNOWN] They do not deserve such a politics as has been handed to them in the past few decades.

1467
03:05:02,310 --> 03:05:14,910
[SPEAKER_16] Therefore, the members of TISZA pledge to close that historical era which repeatedly pitted Hungarians against each other.

1468
03:05:15,290 --> 03:05:23,110
[SPEAKER_16] We undertake a joint commitment that Hungary will once again become a stronger country, one in which the Hungarian people can take pride,

1469
03:05:23,110 --> 03:05:27,570
[SPEAKER_16] but what unites us will be stronger than what divides us.

1470
03:05:27,730 --> 03:05:33,810
[SPEAKER_16] That we will once again learn to think of ourselves as a nation,

1471
03:05:33,890 --> 03:05:45,290
[SPEAKER_16] even if we come from different places, carry different experiences, or voted for different political communities.

1472
03:05:59,730 --> 03:06:10,650
[SPEAKER_16] We pledge that in the coming years, we will strengthen the language of trust, humanity, and shared patriotism in this country.

1473
03:06:10,810 --> 03:06:21,890
[SPEAKER_16] That public life will once again be permeated by cooperation, curiosity, mutual respect, and a sense of shared responsibility.

1474
03:06:21,890 --> 03:06:31,430
[SPEAKER_16] That Hungary will finally become a common home for every Hungarian, where everyone can feel they have a place in the nation.

1475
03:06:32,550 --> 03:06:38,290
[SPEAKER_16] We pledge that we will respect the dignity of every Hungarian.

1476
03:06:39,010 --> 03:06:46,470
[SPEAKER_16] The dignity of those who supported us, and the dignity of those who believed in another political community.

1477
03:06:46,910 --> 03:06:50,630
[SPEAKER_16] Because belonging to the nation is a shared fate,

1478
03:06:50,630 --> 03:06:56,390
[SPEAKER_16] a shared language, a shared story, and a shared responsibility.

1479
03:06:56,890 --> 03:07:09,650
[SPEAKER_16] We pledge to build a country where politics is once again able to give people hope, security, and shared goals.

1480
03:07:10,130 --> 03:07:19,130
[SPEAKER_16] A Hungary where families, friends, and communities are once again able to talk to one another,

1481
03:07:19,130 --> 03:07:26,330
[SPEAKER_16] to listen to one another and to rejoice together in belonging to the same country.

1482
03:07:26,710 --> 03:07:34,350
[SPEAKER_16] And we also pledge that at every decision we make, we will remember that historical moment,

1483
03:07:35,130 --> 03:07:42,490
[SPEAKER_16] when millions of Hungarians declared that Hungary wants to begin a new era,

1484
03:07:43,130 --> 03:07:49,110
[SPEAKER_16] an era of a freer, more humane, hopeful, and cooperative,

1485
03:07:49,110 --> 03:07:52,290
[SPEAKER_16] country proud of one another.

1486
03:08:03,210 --> 03:08:06,010
[SPEAKER_16] Honorable colleagues!

1487
03:08:07,110 --> 03:08:13,310
[SPEAKER_16] After facing the truth, but only after that, retribution is needed.

1488
03:08:14,110 --> 03:08:19,090
[UNKNOWN] Retribution is the mutual rebuilding of democracy.

1489
03:08:19,110 --> 03:08:20,310
[SPEAKER_16] This is one of its fundamental prerequisites.

1490
03:08:21,110 --> 03:08:27,990
[SPEAKER_16] The declaration that Hungary cannot begin a new era on the basis of concealed crimes,

1491
03:08:29,110 --> 03:08:35,590
[SPEAKER_16] hidden contracts, public resources put at the service of private interests,

1492
03:08:35,590 --> 03:08:40,490
[SPEAKER_16] and power abuses left without consequences.

1493
03:08:41,270 --> 03:08:44,990
[SPEAKER_16] The Hungarian people have the right to know,

1494
03:08:44,990 --> 03:08:50,770
[SPEAKER_16] how the power structure of the past decades functioned.

1495
03:08:50,910 --> 03:08:54,690
[SPEAKER_16] They have the right to know what decisions led to the situation,

1496
03:08:54,690 --> 03:08:58,070
[SPEAKER_16] where a significant part of the nation’s common wealth

1497
03:08:58,070 --> 03:09:04,070
[SPEAKER_16] became concentrated in the hands of a narrow political and economic elite.

1498
03:09:04,530 --> 03:09:10,010
[UNKNOWN] They have the right to know how public money became private property.

1499
03:09:10,070 --> 03:09:13,990
[SPEAKER_16] How state assets became political influence.

1500
03:09:14,990 --> 03:09:19,330
[SPEAKER_16] How public procurement became a feudal system.

1501
03:09:19,510 --> 03:09:22,790
[SPEAKER_16] How concessions became privileges.

1502
03:09:23,990 --> 03:09:27,690
[SPEAKER_16] following the formation of the new National Assembly,

1503
03:09:27,690 --> 03:09:31,050
[SPEAKER_16] we will submit it among the first items,

1504
03:09:31,050 --> 03:09:37,390
[SPEAKER_16] the law on the National Office for the Recovery and Protection of State Assets.

