1540
03:14:28,890 --> 03:14:31,230
[SPEAKER_16] This is the essence of justice.

1541
03:14:32,630 --> 03:14:36,290
[UNKNOWN] [UNKNOWN] And there are still some things here that we need to talk about.

1542
03:14:37,030 --> 03:14:53,070
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Over the past years, dozens of public institutions have lost the public trust in their independence.

1543
03:14:53,070 --> 03:15:04,590
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] They played with it, or because they never took it seriously in the first place, they emptied out the system of checks and balances.

1544
03:15:06,150 --> 03:15:09,710
[UNKNOWN] [UNKNOWN] They left the nation to fend for itself in times of trouble.

1545
03:15:10,410 --> 03:15:23,050
[UNKNOWN] [UNKNOWN] Therefore, I now address the holders of public office in this house of Hungarian democracy and constitutional order,

1546
03:15:23,070 --> 03:15:34,610
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] those in positions of dignity, those in leadership roles at institutions who have become political servants of the previous regime or always were.

1547
03:15:35,670 --> 03:15:49,030
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Let them finally have the courage to face their own responsibility and step aside from the path of Hungary's democratic renewal.

1548
03:15:49,190 --> 03:15:53,050
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Resign now, but at the very latest.

1549
03:15:53,070 --> 03:15:59,190
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] By May 31st, and start salting it right away, Tamás Sulyog.

1550
03:16:25,070 --> 03:16:45,150
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] That Tamás Sulyog, whom we heard today speaking on behalf of the entire nation, speaking about the rule of law, expressing concern for the rule of law for the first time after two years.

1551
