03:24:17,580 --> 03:24:18,080
[UNKNOWN] THE TORONTO AUDIENCE

1602
03:24:18,080 --> 03:24:23,820
[UNKNOWN] THE TORONTO AUDIENCE

1603
03:24:23,820 --> 03:24:24,780
[SPEAKER_16] Fellow citizens!

1604
03:24:26,100 --> 03:24:35,820
[SPEAKER_16] The gravest sin of the past few years was that politics deliberately turned Hungarians against each other.

1605
03:24:36,120 --> 03:24:38,100
[SPEAKER_16] Families, friendships,

1606
03:24:38,100 --> 03:24:45,300
[SPEAKER_16] communities were torn apart by hatred, stigmatization, and constant incitement.

1607
03:24:45,660 --> 03:24:53,380
[SPEAKER_16] Millions of people were pushed into a state of fear and spiritual uncertainty.

1608
03:24:53,880 --> 03:25:00,400
[SPEAKER_16] Children grew up amid constant political hate campaigns.

1609
03:25:01,240 --> 03:25:04,740
[SPEAKER_16] The elderly feared the future.

1610
03:25:04,740 --> 03:25:10,400
[SPEAKER_16] The war, each other, their neighbors.

1611
03:25:10,400 --> 03:25:21,740
[SPEAKER_16] An entire nation’s spiritual state was poisoned by that politics which cynically toyed with the creation of artificial fear.

1612
03:25:21,920 --> 03:25:29,360
[SPEAKER_16] Hungary’s state can never again do this to its own citizens. Never again.

1613
03:25:29,520 --> 03:25:34,040
[SPEAKER_16] April 12 marked the end of this era.

1614
03:25:34,040 --> 03:25:35,920
[SPEAKER_16] Once and for all.

1615
03:25:36,620 --> 03:25:37,480
[UNKNOWN] cucumbers

1616
03:25:51,580 --> 03:26:02,420
[UNKNOWN] In Hungarian history, such moments are rare, when a nation so clearly and powerfully decides in favor of change.

1617
03:26:02,420 --> 03:26:13,860
[UNKNOWN] The Hungarian people have now given themselves a historical opportunity, and it is our duty to preserve this opportunity, to navigate it well.

1618
03:26:15,120 --> 03:26:23,700
[SPEAKER_16] Therefore, I would now like to ask something of every Hungarian who has voted trust in us.

1619
03:26:24,720 --> 03:26:33,160
[SPEAKER_16] Let us learn together from the mistakes of the past, do not leave politics to the politicians.

1620
03:26:34,060 --> 03:26:51,980
[UNKNOWN] Watch us, hold us accountable, demand accountability for our promises, debate with us, and never allow anyone to return with the mandate that you have given.

1621
03:26:53,700 --> 03:27:01,220
[UNKNOWN] [UNKNOWN] And I ask that we begin together the great work of reuniting the nation.

1622
03:27:02,360 --> 03:27:10,220
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Let us knock on each other's doors, look each other in the eye, and find out what binds us together.

1623
03:27:11,360 --> 03:27:23,680
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Let us visit, let us see that neighbor, that friend, that family member with whom we have not been able to talk about politics for years without it causing offense,

1624
03:27:23,700 --> 03:27:24,820
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] or anger.

1625
03:27:26,140 --> 03:27:36,700
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] And this time, let us not try to convince each other, not try to win another political argument, but simply try to understand one another.

1626
03:27:37,500 --> 03:27:48,880
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Let us tell each other that even though we voted for different parties, we still love this beautiful country just the same, we still want safety for our children,

1627
03:27:49,040 --> 03:27:53,020
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] just the same peaceful, functioning, fair country.

1628
03:27:53,700 --> 03:27:56,180
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] We want to live in a humane, humanly just country.

1629
03:27:57,200 --> 03:28:02,560
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Let us relearn the simplest rules of living together in a shared nation.

1630
03:28:03,520 --> 03:28:14,900
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] That it is indeed possible to argue with one another without wanting to wipe the other off the face of the earth, to expel them from the entire nation, from its body.

1631
03:28:15,060 --> 03:28:22,380
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] That it is possible to think as members of a common homeland despite political differences.

1632
03:28:22,380 --> 03:28:31,500
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] That it is possible to love Hungary equally, even while thinking completely differently about the world and politics.

1633
03:28:32,000 --> 03:28:43,300
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Therefore, national reconciliation does not depend on a single law, a single speech, or a single electoral victory.

1634
03:28:43,740 --> 03:28:51,980
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] It depends on whether the Hungarian people will once again be able to turn to one another with trust.

1635
03:28:52,380 --> 03:28:58,300
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Whether we will be able to once again assume good intentions in one another.

1636
03:28:58,660 --> 03:29:08,280
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Whether we will be able to once again listen to each other without immediately seeing a traitor or an enemy in the other.

1637
03:29:08,840 --> 03:29:15,520
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Whether we will be able to once again view Hungary as a shared story.

1638
03:29:16,240 --> 03:29:19,980
[UNKNOWN] [UNKNOWN] I believe, I believe we will be able to.

1639
03:29:19,980 --> 03:29:28,900
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] In fact, the Hungarian nation is waiting for the beginning of this shared story as one people.

1640
03:29:30,880 --> 03:29:31,960
[UNKNOWN] cucumbers

1641
03:29:31,960 --> 03:29:31,960
