1642
03:29:44,480 --> 03:29:52,700
[SPEAKER_16] Honfitársaim! The soon-to-be-formed Tisza government will be the government of every Hungarian.

1643
03:29:52,820 --> 03:30:00,920
[SPEAKER_16] Our goal is that every Hungarian person becomes a true citizen of this country.

1644
03:30:00,920 --> 03:30:20,620
[SPEAKER_16] Not just the wealthy, not just the influential, not just the politically loyal, but everyone who lives in this country, works, raises children, pays taxes, hopes, and wants a future for themselves.

1645
03:30:20,960 --> 03:30:26,120
[SPEAKER_16] Because the homeland is not a privilege. The homeland is a shared home.

1646
03:30:27,320 --> 03:30:30,420
[SPEAKER_16] And the Hungarian state must finally turn toward every person.

1647
03:30:30,920 --> 03:30:39,340
[SPEAKER_16] With the same respect, the same dignity, and the same responsibility.

1648
03:30:40,520 --> 03:30:42,460
[SPEAKER_16] Honored fellow citizens!

1649
03:30:43,020 --> 03:30:53,720
[UNKNOWN] For me, a free Hungary means what Adi Endre expressed so well: every person is royalty.

1650
03:30:54,800 --> 03:30:59,760
[SPEAKER_16] It means that in this country, every person matters.

1651
03:31:00,920 --> 03:31:12,220
[SPEAKER_16] Every Hungarian has the right to feel that the Hungarian state works for them, protects them, and respects their dignity.

1652
03:31:14,500 --> 03:31:27,400
[SPEAKER_16] Citizen, the little boy from Sükösd, who may be visiting Budapest for the first time, and certainly for the first time in the most beautiful building in the world.

1653
03:31:27,400 --> 03:31:35,500
[SPEAKER_16] And who looks at this country with the same curiosity as any child in a big city.

1654
03:31:36,600 --> 03:31:48,840
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for him too, because he deserves the best school, the best teacher, and the same opportunity for success.

1655
03:32:01,740 --> 03:32:10,120
[SPEAKER_16] Citizen, Martin, who ran away from the foster home, whom the state left alone too often.

1656
03:32:11,040 --> 03:32:14,140
[UNKNOWN] Citizen, someone who needs to be protected.

1657
03:32:14,940 --> 03:32:25,320
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for him too, because he has the right to live in safety, in love, and with dignity, to grow.

1658
03:32:26,340 --> 03:32:27,380
[UNKNOWN] Citizen, Martin, who ran away from the foster home, whom the state left alone too often.

1659
03:32:27,400 --> 03:32:37,420
[SPEAKER_16] And the four-children mother, who counts every month how much money she still has left from her salary,

1660
03:32:38,120 --> 03:32:43,880
[SPEAKER_16] while at the same time working, raising children, hoping, and trying to find her place.

1661
03:32:45,060 --> 03:32:54,600
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for her as well, because her work keeps this country alive just as much as anyone else's, for example here.

1662
03:33:00,120 --> 03:33:00,880
[UNKNOWN] Thank you.

1663
03:33:05,300 --> 03:33:19,380
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is also that elderly man who, after forty years of honest work, wants nothing else but peace, security, and a little respect at the end of his life.

1664
03:33:19,540 --> 03:33:26,520
[SPEAKER_16] And a citizen is also that retired woman who only longs for not having to choose between healer and cure anymore.

1665
03:33:27,400 --> 03:33:35,220
[SPEAKER_16] Between instruments, food, or heating. We will work for her as well.

1666
03:33:44,260 --> 03:33:50,260
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is also that farmer in the countryside who has been cultivating the same land for generations.

1667
03:33:50,440 --> 03:33:56,740
[SPEAKER_16] And a citizen is the young entrepreneur who believes that with honest work,

1668
03:33:57,400 --> 03:33:59,540
[SPEAKER_16] it is also possible to build a future in Hungary.

1669
03:34:00,300 --> 03:34:02,280
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for him as well.

1670
03:34:03,300 --> 03:34:11,520
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is the teacher who still believes in the vocation of education despite all the difficulties.

1671
03:34:12,300 --> 03:34:18,760
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is the caregiver who works night after night for people's lives.

1672
03:34:18,960 --> 03:34:26,960
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is the police officer, the firefighter, the paramedic, the social worker.

1673
03:34:27,400 --> 03:34:34,840
[SPEAKER_16] Who serves the country even when he often does not receive the proper respect himself.

1674
03:34:35,140 --> 03:34:38,940
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for them as well, for all of them.

1675
03:34:48,500 --> 03:34:55,240
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is also the Hungarian living abroad who belongs to this nation just as much.

1676
03:34:55,360 --> 03:34:57,380
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is the police officer who, despite all the difficulties, still works night after night for people's lives.

1677
03:34:57,380 --> 03:34:58,780
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for them as well, for all of them.

1678
03:34:58,780 --> 03:35:10,480
[SPEAKER_16] A citizen is also the young person who had to leave the country, but who, with every call home, thinks of Hungary with pain and love.

1679
03:35:14,620 --> 03:35:24,220
[UNKNOWN] A citizen is the police officer who, with every call home, thinks of Hungary with pain and love.

1680
03:35:24,360 --> 03:35:27,020
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for them as well, for all of them.

1681
03:35:27,020 --> 03:35:36,120
[SPEAKER_16] No one shall suffer disadvantage because of their origin, their love, or their political opinion.

1682
03:35:37,020 --> 03:35:39,620
[SPEAKER_16] We will work for every Hungarian person.

1683
03:35:41,020 --> 03:35:41,600
[UNKNOWN] We will work for every Hungarian person.

1684
03:35:43,840 --> 03:35:44,980
[UNKNOWN] Because dear colleagues, if it is not possible to go home, it is not possible to go home.

1685
03:35:53,020 --> 03:35:57,000
[SPEAKER_16] Because dear colleagues, if it is not possible to go home, it is not possible to go home.

1686
03:35:57,000 --> 03:36:00,260
[SPEAKER_16] And there will be no fewer privileges.

1687
03:36:01,000 --> 03:36:05,100
[SPEAKER_16] Our wonderful homeland is the common home of every Hungarian person.

1688
03:36:05,640 --> 03:36:10,480
[UNKNOWN] Esteemed fellow citizens, a fresh start is needed.

1689
03:36:11,140 --> 03:36:20,620
[SPEAKER_16] Step by step, brick by brick, we will rebuild what the past decades have torn down.

1690
03:36:20,720 --> 03:36:26,980
[SPEAKER_16] The state, trust, public services, respect, and the various lives.

1691
03:36:26,980 --> 03:36:26,980
[SPEAKER_16] 

