03:36:26,980 --> 03:36:26,980
[SPEAKER_16] 

1693
03:36:27,000 --> 03:36:32,040
[SPEAKER_16] The fair competition, national unity, and hope.

1694
03:36:32,740 --> 03:36:38,740
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a Hungary where our fellow citizens living in poverty

1695
03:36:38,740 --> 03:36:41,940
[SPEAKER_16] once again have the chance to rise up.

1696
03:36:43,000 --> 03:36:48,140
[SPEAKER_16] Where the fate of a single child is not sealed by where they are born,

1697
03:36:49,000 --> 03:36:53,300
[SPEAKER_16] what kind of family they come from, or which town in the country they grow up in.

1698
03:36:53,300 --> 03:36:57,660
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a country where the elderly are respected citizens in their final years, where the pension once again provides security,

1699
03:36:57,660 --> 03:37:04,000
[SPEAKER_16] and where no one, after a lifetime of work, has to choose between heating and food.

1700
03:37:04,820 --> 03:37:10,920
[SPEAKER_16] és ahol egy életmunkája után senkinek sem kell választani a fűtés vagy az élelmiszer között.

1701
03:37:11,700 --> 03:37:18,800
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a Hungary where the healthcare system provides timely assistance,

1702
03:37:18,800 --> 03:37:24,440
[SPEAKER_16] where people's fate is decided by professionals,

1703
03:37:25,520 --> 03:37:33,280
[SPEAKER_16] preferably qualified professionals, functioning hospitals, accessible family doctors,

1704
03:37:33,920 --> 03:37:41,120
[SPEAKER_16] respected nurses and doctors. We will build a Hungary

1705
03:37:41,120 --> 03:37:46,900
[SPEAKER_16] where daycare, kindergarten, and school once again become the gates to upward mobility,

1706
03:37:47,060 --> 03:37:48,460
[SPEAKER_16] where nannies,

1707
03:37:48,460 --> 03:37:56,160
[SPEAKER_16] kindergarten teachers, and school teachers are respected individuals and children are not statistics,

1708
03:37:56,160 --> 03:38:02,700
[UNKNOWN] where knowledge is not a privilege and where even a talented young person born into a poor family

1709
03:38:02,700 --> 03:38:06,620
[SPEAKER_16] will also find the path open toward success.

1710
03:38:17,480 --> 03:38:23,480
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a Hungary where child protection truly means protection.

1711
03:38:23,620 --> 03:38:28,220
[SPEAKER_16] We will uncover the child abuse cases of the past years,

1712
03:38:28,380 --> 03:38:35,180
[SPEAKER_16] strengthen child protection, and make children's safety clear,

1713
03:38:35,240 --> 03:38:36,600
[SPEAKER_16] the protection of children, child abuse, child abuse,

1714
03:38:36,620 --> 03:38:38,840
[SPEAKER_16] is one of the most important duties of the Hungarian state.

1715
03:38:39,000 --> 03:38:45,640
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a Hungary that once again welcomes Hungarians living abroad,

1716
03:38:46,540 --> 03:38:51,300
[SPEAKER_16] where once again hundreds of thousands will feel it is worth returning home,

1717
03:38:51,980 --> 03:38:59,100
[SPEAKER_16] because one can also live safely, have children, build a home,

1718
03:38:59,100 --> 03:39:05,600
[SPEAKER_16] plan for the future here, and where their compatriots who have moved abroad remain part of the life of the Hungarian nation, the life of the Hungarian nation, the life of the Hungarian nation,

1719
03:39:06,220 --> 03:39:06,600
[SPEAKER_16] and the country counts on them as part of its shared future.

1720
03:39:06,620 --> 03:39:13,060
[SPEAKER_16] részei maradnak, akikre az ország a közös jövőinek részeként számít.

1721
03:39:13,420 --> 03:39:19,200
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a country where work once again ensures a decent standard of living,

1722
03:39:20,060 --> 03:39:24,780
[SPEAKER_16] where wages gradually catch up to European levels,

1723
03:39:25,620 --> 03:39:30,360
[SPEAKER_16] the tax system becomes fairer and more predictable,

1724
03:39:31,220 --> 03:39:35,920
[SPEAKER_16] the energy of businesses is directed toward development, innovation and

1725
03:39:35,920 --> 03:39:45,100
[SPEAKER_16] job creation, and where the growth of the Hungarian economy finally benefits Hungarian families as well.

1726
03:39:45,760 --> 03:39:58,700
[SPEAKER_16] In the past years, hundreds of billions were spent supporting foreign investments

1727
03:39:58,700 --> 03:40:08,140
[SPEAKER_16] that treated Hungary as a simple assembly and investment zone.

1728
03:40:09,260 --> 03:40:16,880
[SPEAKER_16] Profit became more important than people, the natural environment, and the safety of local communities.

1729
03:40:16,980 --> 03:40:24,040
[SPEAKER_16] And it was the most grateful Hungarian government that allowed this, indeed, supported it, and still supports it.

1730
03:40:24,820 --> 03:40:27,980
[UNKNOWN] There were companies that behaved in Hungary

1731
03:40:28,700 --> 03:40:36,160
[SPEAKER_16] as if the same rules that apply to Hungarian citizens and companies did not apply to them.

1732
03:40:37,300 --> 03:40:46,020
[SPEAKER_16] And they were able to do this because the most grateful Hungarian government allowed it, indeed, supported it, and was proud of it.

1733
03:40:46,560 --> 03:40:48,700
[SPEAKER_16] We will put an end to this.

1734
03:40:48,760 --> 03:40:53,080
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a Hungary where the investor is everything.

1735
03:40:53,080 --> 03:40:58,000
[SPEAKER_16] Investors respect our laws, our environment,

1736
03:40:58,000 --> 03:41:03,060
[SPEAKER_16] our employees, and the safety of our local communities.

1737
03:41:17,540 --> 03:41:23,300
[UNKNOWN] We will build a Hungary where public funds are once again public funds,

1738
03:41:24,420 --> 03:41:27,140
[SPEAKER_16] where public property is once again national wealth.

1739
03:41:28,000 --> 03:41:32,040
[SPEAKER_16] And where no one can ever again think that they can obtain what belongs to every Hungarian through political connections,

1740
03:41:32,040 --> 03:41:39,400
[SPEAKER_16] party loyalty, or personal loyalty.

1741
03:41:39,720 --> 03:41:48,780
[SPEAKER_16] We will build a Hungary that once again has dignity in Europe and in the world,

1742
03:41:49,600 --> 03:41:56,920
[SPEAKER_16] that does not drift out of the federal systems it has chosen itself, and does not grovel.

1743
03:41:58,000 --> 03:42:07,040
[SPEAKER_16] It does not grovel before foreign interests, and does not confuse sovereignty with isolation.

1744
03:42:08,140 --> 03:42:20,720
[SPEAKER_16] Hungary's place is in Europe, and we are building a strong, respected, European Hungary that clearly represents its own interests.

1745
03:42:20,920 --> 03:42:27,920
[UNKNOWN] We will be the government of national self-determination, restoring Hungary's international credibility,

1746
03:42:28,680 --> 03:42:40,160
[SPEAKER_16] rebuilding our federal relationships, and bringing back the EU funds that belong to the Hungarian people and Hungarian businesses.

1747
03:42:40,500 --> 03:42:41,880
[SPEAKER_16] We must say it out loud...

1748
03:42:51,920 --> 03:42:57,820
[SPEAKER_16] We declare that the country of Saint Stephen is not a pass-through house.

1749
03:42:58,000 --> 03:43:04,940
[SPEAKER_16] Hungary has been the homeland of the Hungarians in the Carpathian Basin for 1100 years.

1750
03:43:06,140 --> 03:43:14,740
[UNKNOWN] We are open to every person who comes to us with peace, respect, and a spirit of cooperation.

1751
03:43:14,840 --> 03:43:26,640
[SPEAKER_16] But those who want to exploit this country, who want to establish influence, subjugation, or dependency in Hungary,

1752
03:43:26,640 --> 03:43:34,320
[SPEAKER_16] we will deal with them most decisively. We will act most decisively against them.

1753
03:43:34,920 --> 03:43:40,960
[SPEAKER_16] Hungary will once again truly be a sovereign country, and it will remain so.

1754
03:43:41,000 --> 03:43:47,380
[SPEAKER_16] This will be the functional Hungary, and this will be the humane Hungary.

1755
03:43:47,800 --> 03:43:52,640
[SPEAKER_16] Functional, because the state will finally do its job.

1756
03:43:54,260 --> 03:43:56,620
[UNKNOWN] It heals, it teaches, it carries out its duties.

1757
03:43:56,620 --> 03:43:56,620
[SPEAKER_16] 

1758
03:43:56,620 --> 03:43:56,620
[SPEAKER_16] 

1759
03:43:56,620 --> 03:43:56,620
[SPEAKER_16] 

1760
03:43:56,620 --> 03:43:56,620
[SPEAKER_16] 

1761
03:43:56,620 --> 03:44:08,080
[SPEAKER_16] It protects, organizes transportation, provides security, creates opportunities, and accounts accurately for the assets entrusted to it.

1762
03:44:08,480 --> 03:44:16,400
[UNKNOWN] It is humane because it does not forget that behind every decision there are human fates.

1763
03:44:17,260 --> 03:44:24,840
[SPEAKER_16] Children, parents, the elderly, the sick, workers, teachers, caregivers,

1764
03:44:24,840 --> 03:44:31,100
[SPEAKER_16] law enforcement officers, social workers, entrepreneurs, farmers, students,

1765
03:44:31,320 --> 03:44:35,520
[SPEAKER_16] Hungarians living in the country and abroad.

1766
03:44:36,860 --> 03:44:39,440
[SPEAKER_16] Honorable colleagues!

1767
03:44:39,560 --> 03:44:47,180
[SPEAKER_16] I ask you, whether you sit in the governing party or the opposition faction,

1768
03:44:47,400 --> 03:44:54,200
[SPEAKER_16] to understand the message of the election that stands behind us,

1769
03:44:54,200 --> 03:44:56,740
[UNKNOWN] and its historical weight.

1770
03:44:57,820 --> 03:45:05,940
[UNKNOWN] The governing party faction, which now holds a two-thirds majority, has a particularly great responsibility.

1771
03:45:06,260 --> 03:45:11,960
[SPEAKER_16] In Hungarian history, it has happened too often that a political community

1772
03:45:11,960 --> 03:45:19,380
[UNKNOWN] confused electoral victory with moral and political infallibility.

1773
03:45:20,200 --> 03:45:23,220
[SPEAKER_16] We must not commit this mistake.

1774
03:45:24,200 --> 03:45:28,340
[SPEAKER_16] Therefore, we regard even our own power as limited.

1775
03:45:28,840 --> 03:45:35,180
[SPEAKER_16] We will initiate a comprehensive review of Hungary's constitutional system,

1776
03:45:36,200 --> 03:45:45,240
[SPEAKER_16] in order to ensure that power does not concentrate to such an extent in this country again.

1777
03:45:45,440 --> 03:45:50,480
[UNKNOWN] We will strengthen the system of checks and balances.

1778
03:45:50,900 --> 03:45:53,180
[SPEAKER_16] We will restore the institutions.

1779
03:45:54,200 --> 03:45:57,400
[SPEAKER_16] The true independence of institutions.

1780
03:45:58,200 --> 03:46:03,220
[SPEAKER_16] And we will initiate the limitation of the number of prime ministerial terms.

1781
03:46:18,200 --> 03:46:20,200
[SPEAKER_16] Because in a democratic country

1782
03:46:21,200 --> 03:46:24,180
[SPEAKER_16] power must always be within limits.

1783
03:46:24,200 --> 03:46:28,280
[SPEAKER_16] Freedom is not enough to be won.

1784
03:46:28,280 --> 03:46:32,300
[SPEAKER_16] It must also be protected from the current power.

1785
03:46:32,380 --> 03:46:35,780
[SPEAKER_16] And I especially address my fellow parliamentarians,

1786
03:46:36,000 --> 03:46:40,400
[SPEAKER_16] to enter this house every day

1787
03:46:41,400 --> 03:46:48,120
[SPEAKER_16] so that their own selves from one and a half to two years ago would be proud of them.

1788
03:46:49,660 --> 03:46:52,280
[UNKNOWN] Remember that person,

1789
03:46:52,280 --> 03:46:56,760
[SPEAKER_16] who recently stood behind a counter in a square,

1790
03:46:56,860 --> 03:47:02,080
[SPEAKER_16] often uncertainly, often fearfully,

1791
03:47:02,240 --> 03:47:08,380
[UNKNOWN] but still resolutely, because there was still one last chance left

1792
03:47:08,380 --> 03:47:10,260
[SPEAKER_16] for this beautiful country.

1793
03:47:11,040 --> 03:47:15,880
[UNKNOWN] Remember how you felt then,

1794
03:47:16,020 --> 03:47:20,300
[SPEAKER_16] when the Hungarian public life seemed hopeless.

1795
03:47:20,300 --> 03:47:29,980
[SPEAKER_16] When you thought that perhaps after 2026, you might not even have a future in this beautiful country.

1796
03:47:30,700 --> 03:47:34,700
[SPEAKER_16] Let this memory be present in every decision you make.

1797
03:47:35,400 --> 03:47:38,820
[SPEAKER_16] Surround yourselves with people

1798
03:47:38,980 --> 03:47:44,040
[SPEAKER_16] who remind you of this every single day.

1799
03:47:44,640 --> 03:47:47,980
[SPEAKER_16] Because the first temptation of power is always

1800
03:47:47,980 --> 03:47:53,980
[SPEAKER_16] to make us forget where we came from and where we set out to go.

1801
03:47:54,540 --> 03:47:57,020
[SPEAKER_16] And we have asked for and accepted all of this.

1802
03:47:57,580 --> 03:48:03,160
[SPEAKER_16] But our opposition colleagues also bear a great responsibility,

1803
03:48:03,260 --> 03:48:05,200
[SPEAKER_16] one they must face.

1804
03:48:05,980 --> 03:48:10,420
[SPEAKER_16] Therefore, let me now address the former ruling party members,

1805
03:48:10,980 --> 03:48:13,600
[SPEAKER_16] the Fidesz representatives present here.

1806
03:48:14,180 --> 03:48:16,980
[SPEAKER_16] We naturally accept the legal outcome of the elections,

1807
03:48:17,980 --> 03:48:19,640
[SPEAKER_16] and we begin parliamentary work with mutual respect.

1808
03:48:19,720 --> 03:48:24,880
[SPEAKER_16] However, there is one issue we cannot pass by in silence.

1809
03:48:25,100 --> 03:48:30,020
[SPEAKER_16] Ág Péter.

1810
03:48:31,560 --> 03:48:32,820
[SPEAKER_16] The circumstances surrounding Ág Péter’s mandate point to a single electoral district.

1811
03:48:34,660 --> 03:48:43,560
[SPEAKER_16] A political maneuver appeared there,

1812
03:48:43,880 --> 03:48:47,300
[SPEAKER_16] which is unworthy of Hungarian democracy,

1813
03:48:47,980 --> 03:48:51,680
[SPEAKER_16] and which must and will be permanently removed from public life.

1814
03:48:51,680 --> 03:48:59,020
[SPEAKER_16] The citizens of Northern Vas County have no reason to fear.

1815
03:48:59,920 --> 03:49:05,900
[SPEAKER_16] They cannot be subjected to any political retaliation or disadvantage.

1816
03:49:06,600 --> 03:49:10,620
[SPEAKER_16] Their interests will indeed be represented in this house.

1817
03:49:10,780 --> 03:49:16,580
[SPEAKER_16] Their interests will continue to be represented,

1818
03:49:16,580 --> 03:49:20,460
[SPEAKER_16] even if we clearly state our commitment to the defense of Hungarian democracy and the rule of law,

1819
03:49:20,600 --> 03:49:26,340
[SPEAKER_16] against manipulative, petty, and illegal election methods.

1820
03:49:26,520 --> 03:49:33,900
[SPEAKER_16] hogy manipulatív, piti, jogellenes választási módszerekre

1821
03:49:34,580 --> 03:49:39,440
[SPEAKER_16] It is impossible to build a rule of law and democracy on such foundations.

1822
03:49:39,740 --> 03:49:44,320
[SPEAKER_16] It is particularly serious that in this campaign, right here

1823
03:49:44,320 --> 03:49:46,560
[UNKNOWN] an almost Hungarian democratic figure,

1824
03:49:46,580 --> 03:49:51,360
[SPEAKER_16] has managed to cast doubt on his Hungarian identity,

1825
03:49:52,580 --> 03:49:58,440
[SPEAKER_16] despite—or precisely because of—his birth in Upper Hungary

1826
03:49:59,580 --> 03:50:02,800
[SPEAKER_16] he is a member of the same Hungarian nation,

1827
03:50:02,980 --> 03:50:09,080
[SPEAKER_16] just like any of us in this room, dear Lázár János.

1828
03:50:09,320 --> 03:50:10,700
[SPEAKER_16] Stromba Victoria!

1829
03:50:20,400 --> 03:50:21,800
[UNKNOWN] Thank you very much!

1830
03:50:47,700 --> 03:50:51,680
[SPEAKER_16] If the representative thinks so, I am happy to give her the floor,

1831
03:50:51,680 --> 03:50:53,540
[SPEAKER_04] or to the chairperson for an apology.

1832
03:50:53,740 --> 03:50:59,220
[SPEAKER_16] Stromba Victoria’s story warns us

1833
03:50:59,420 --> 03:51:06,400
[SPEAKER_16] where it leads when politics repeatedly seeks to determine

1834
03:51:06,400 --> 03:51:10,240
[SPEAKER_16] who belongs to the nation and who does not.

1835
03:51:10,840 --> 03:51:15,940
[SPEAKER_16] We will put an end to this era, in fact it has already ended,

1836
03:51:15,940 --> 03:51:17,500
[SPEAKER_16] on April 12th.

1837
03:51:17,780 --> 03:51:20,240
[SPEAKER_16] Honorable Fidesz representatives!

1838
03:51:20,940 --> 03:51:23,900
[SPEAKER_16] You now represent the marginalized, disappointed,

1839
03:51:23,980 --> 03:51:28,940
[SPEAKER_16] often uncertain citizens in this house.

1840
03:51:29,680 --> 03:51:31,040
[SPEAKER_16] jelentik ebben a házban.

1841
03:51:31,400 --> 03:51:33,340
[SPEAKER_16] We respect this.

1842
03:51:33,600 --> 03:51:39,200
[SPEAKER_16] The election result gave us a clear mandate to govern,

1843
03:51:39,360 --> 03:51:45,880
[SPEAKER_16] but this does not make any less important the millions of Hungarians

1844
03:51:45,880 --> 03:51:51,960
[SPEAKER_16] who believed in a different political community, made a different decision,

1845
03:51:52,080 --> 03:51:54,820
[SPEAKER_16] and envisioned a different future for Hungary.

1846
03:51:55,360 --> 03:52:01,520
[SPEAKER_16] Naturally, you primarily represent them, and we also represent them,

1847
03:52:01,680 --> 03:52:04,740
[SPEAKER_16] but this also makes your responsibility historic.

1848
03:52:04,900 --> 03:52:09,240
[SPEAKER_16] The reunification of the nation also requires you.

1849
03:52:09,580 --> 03:52:15,860
[SPEAKER_16] In order for Hungary to start with a clean slate, it is in our common interest, over the past 20 years,

1850
03:52:15,860 --> 03:52:22,020
[SPEAKER_16] to uncover the sins of the past 20 years, to reveal the agent files.

1851
03:52:34,860 --> 03:52:40,040
[SPEAKER_16] It is in our common interest to uncover the fate of public assets,

1852
03:52:40,060 --> 03:52:45,840
[UNKNOWN] and the establishment of a national property recovery and protection authority,

1853
03:52:45,860 --> 03:52:47,260
[SPEAKER_16] and the setting up of the office as well.

1854
03:52:47,460 --> 03:52:50,320
[SPEAKER_16] This is not the concern of a single political side.

1855
03:52:50,800 --> 03:52:55,600
[SPEAKER_16] These are the prerequisites for every Hungarian finally to see

1856
03:52:55,700 --> 03:53:01,360
[SPEAKER_16] what decisions were made, who made them, who carried them out,

1857
03:53:01,740 --> 03:53:05,780
[SPEAKER_16] who benefited from them, and who is burdened with what responsibility.

1858
03:53:08,060 --> 03:53:14,620
[SPEAKER_16] It will have great significance and historical weight that you, the opposition,

1859
03:53:15,860 --> 03:53:20,640
[SPEAKER_16] will take a stand, and how you vote on these issues.

1860
03:53:21,480 --> 03:53:29,760
[SPEAKER_16] Agent files, uncovering the fate of public assets, national property recovery and protection authority.

1861
03:53:29,980 --> 03:53:32,600
[SPEAKER_16] No, my AVH is already in the past, Mr. Representative.

1862
03:53:32,760 --> 03:53:38,700
[SPEAKER_16] That is why I ask you, that is why I ask you, dear Fidesz colleagues in the National Assembly,

1863
03:53:38,800 --> 03:53:45,180
[SPEAKER_16] be our opponents if you deem it appropriate, be our strict critics,

1864
03:53:45,860 --> 03:53:53,300
[SPEAKER_16] if we make mistakes, but also be our partners in making Hungary finally a clean, transparent

1865
03:53:53,300 --> 03:53:56,480
[SPEAKER_16] and a common country for all Hungarians.

1866
03:53:57,860 --> 03:54:02,620
[SPEAKER_16] Those who are sitting in the opposition today can also have a historical role.

1867
03:54:02,740 --> 03:54:12,540
[SPEAKER_16] No less than to show their own voters that from defeat, not further, not additional hatred,

1868
03:54:12,540 --> 03:54:20,260
[SPEAKER_16] but a responsible, constitutional, patriotic opposition can also be born.

1869
03:54:21,440 --> 03:54:25,080
[SPEAKER_16] Distinguished compatriots, Hungarians!

1870
03:54:25,600 --> 03:54:38,000
[SPEAKER_16] In 1990, on the first day of the inaugural session of the newly elected National Assembly at the birth of modern Hungarian democracy,

1871
03:54:38,540 --> 03:54:42,520
[SPEAKER_16] an 88-year-old American stood before the inaugural session of the National Assembly,

1872
03:54:42,520 --> 03:54:50,240
[SPEAKER_16] an elderly emigrant walked up to this pulpit to speak to the representatives.

1873
03:54:50,280 --> 03:54:52,120
[SPEAKER_16] His name was Béla Varga.

1874
03:54:52,360 --> 03:55:03,400
[SPEAKER_16] He was the former president of the 1946, the last freely elected National Assembly before communism.

1875
03:55:03,760 --> 03:55:11,620
[SPEAKER_16] His words, Béla Varga’s words, are just as relevant today as they were back then.

1876
03:55:12,520 --> 03:55:18,340
[SPEAKER_16] Human freedom is not a circumstance, but a task.

1877
03:55:18,460 --> 03:55:28,640
[SPEAKER_16] With the falling of the chains comes the human duty we impose on ourselves.

1878
03:55:29,280 --> 03:55:34,980
[SPEAKER_16] It is sometimes harder to be free than to be a prisoner.

1879
03:55:36,380 --> 03:55:39,740
[SPEAKER_16] I stand before you at a historical moment,

1880
03:55:39,740 --> 03:55:43,280
[SPEAKER_16] and Hungary also stands before a historical moment.

1881
03:55:43,680 --> 03:55:52,040
[SPEAKER_16] On April 12, the Hungarian people decided to take their fate into their own hands.

1882
03:55:52,360 --> 03:56:00,140
[SPEAKER_16] They decided to teach the world that freedom is not a noun, but a verb.

1883
03:56:01,880 --> 03:56:08,860
