2084
04:23:41,620 --> 04:23:46,740
[SPEAKER_11] And this way, the experience of this beautiful day, the memory of this beautiful day, will also reach more people.

2085
04:23:46,740 --> 04:23:48,300
[SPEAKER_11] The more people, the better.

2086
04:23:48,300 --> 04:23:52,380
[SPEAKER_11] We will still have very important tasks this afternoon,

2087
04:23:52,460 --> 04:23:57,960
[SPEAKER_11] because after the representatives from Tisza arrive here at Kossuth Square,

2088
04:23:57,980 --> 04:24:00,620
[SPEAKER_11] young Balázs Elemér will play the piano.

2089
04:24:00,900 --> 04:24:03,880
[SPEAKER_11] After that, Magyar Péter will also arrive with his children.

2090
04:24:03,960 --> 04:24:08,080
[SPEAKER_11] After that, we will listen together to the song "You Are Beautiful, You Are Magnificent, Hungary."

2091
04:24:09,200 --> 04:24:15,740
[SPEAKER_11] And then the event will continue with the ceremonial raising of the flag of Hungary,

2092
04:24:16,740 --> 04:24:17,920
[SPEAKER_11] the ceremony.

2093
04:24:18,260 --> 04:24:24,600
[SPEAKER_11] After this, the ceremony will continue with the song "Magyarország" by Olá Ibolya.

2094
04:24:24,620 --> 04:24:28,960
[SPEAKER_11] A choir will perform this song.

2095
04:24:31,860 --> 04:24:36,180
[SPEAKER_11] Hopefully, Olá Ibolya will also meet Magyar Péter on the stairs.

2096
04:24:36,360 --> 04:24:40,740
[SPEAKER_11] And this opportunity, I think, will be available to everyone at the end of the event,

2097
04:24:41,280 --> 04:24:45,100
[SPEAKER_11] because, as Magyar Péter put it, after the official program ends here,

2098
04:24:45,160 --> 04:24:46,180
[SPEAKER_11] let there be dancing.

2099
04:24:46,240 --> 04:24:46,720
[SPEAKER_11] And this opportunity, I think, will be available to everyone at the end of the event,

2100
04:24:46,720 --> 04:24:51,900
[SPEAKER_11] and to this, a DJ will provide the music for the rest of the day.

2101
04:24:51,960 --> 04:24:58,440
[SPEAKER_11] So, I think we will say goodbye to this Saturday with a very beautiful sunset and a very beautiful day.

2102
04:25:01,720 --> 04:25:08,140
[UNKNOWN] Here on the square, Péter Magyar addresses those present on-site as well.

2103
04:25:08,280 --> 04:25:15,980
[SPEAKER_11] After his recent remarks, he still has something more to say, and he will deliver these live for us right here on Kossuth Square.

2104
04:25:15,980 --> 04:25:27,780
[SPEAKER_11] After that, we will listen to the song "Mi vagyunk a Grund" performed by József Wunderlich, Zsombor Ertl, Dino Benjamin, László Józan, Péter Rejder, Balázs Szántó, András Tóth, and Péter Virág.

2105
04:25:27,960 --> 04:25:34,820
[SPEAKER_11] After that, Karamell will arrive and bring us the recording titled "Szálok a dallal."

2106
04:25:34,960 --> 04:25:40,880
[SPEAKER_11] After that, a surprise performance, a surprise song, and a surprise performer will follow.

2107
04:25:40,940 --> 04:25:44,280
[SPEAKER_11] I was sworn to secrecy, so I cannot reveal it, and I don't know how long this will go on.

2108
04:25:44,380 --> 04:25:45,960
[SPEAKER_11] It might actually be revealed on stage.

2109
04:25:45,980 --> 04:25:47,080
[SPEAKER_11] Everyone will find out soon enough.

2110
04:25:47,160 --> 04:25:58,640
[SPEAKER_11] But a popular performer, one we all greatly love and cherish, is coming to us, and we will listen to one of his iconic recordings.

2111
04:25:58,740 --> 04:26:04,200
[SPEAKER_11] And I think we all know this one by heart, and we will be able to sing it together with him.

2112
04:26:04,600 --> 04:26:15,960
[SPEAKER_11] So, he is arriving, and of course, in this song, he will not be alone as the songwriter and performer, but he will have helpers, namely Szebényi.

