05:17:51,200 --> 05:17:52,560
[SPEAKER_16] Representatives of the Hungarian people!

2496
05:17:57,840 --> 05:18:05,520
[SPEAKER_16] This wonderful day, this story was not written by us, the representatives.

2497
05:18:06,680 --> 05:18:15,120
[SPEAKER_16] It was not written in party headquarters, not prepared by background figures, nor by propaganda machines.

2498
05:18:15,120 --> 05:18:29,060
[SPEAKER_16] You wrote it through work, love of country, hope, concern, determination, and joy.

2499
05:18:30,120 --> 05:18:39,320
[SPEAKER_16] This is now your system change, your homeland, your National Assembly, and we thank you for this!

2500
05:18:49,140 --> 05:19:02,000
[SPEAKER_16] You were the ones who set an example to the world, showing that there is no need to be afraid, that one can rise up and set out on a journey.

2501
05:19:03,440 --> 05:19:12,300
[SPEAKER_16] You showed the world that even if the galley is above and the water is below, the water is still the master.

2502
05:19:36,860 --> 05:19:43,100
[SPEAKER_16] The world learned to say, "The Tisza is overflowing."

2503
05:19:47,680 --> 05:19:54,440
[UNKNOWN] The Tisza is overflowing! The Tisza is overflowing! The Tisza is overflowing!

2504
05:19:54,880 --> 05:19:59,600
[UNKNOWN] The Tisza is overflowing! The Tisza is overflowing! The Tisza is overflowing!

2505
05:20:04,620 --> 05:20:14,540
[SPEAKER_16] Today, dear compatriots, today every freedom-loving person in the world would like to be a little Hungarian.

2506
05:20:16,760 --> 05:20:26,000
[UNKNOWN] Compatriots, for years they tried to teach us that miracles do not exist.

2507
05:20:26,620 --> 05:20:35,540
[SPEAKER_16] They tried to teach us that war is peace, that freedom is servitude, that ignorance is strength,

2508
05:20:35,780 --> 05:20:45,100
[SPEAKER_16] that those who think differently are less Hungarian, less valuable, less drunk, less personal.

2509
05:20:45,120 --> 05:20:50,620
[UNKNOWN] But did this beautiful country succeed? Did it succeed? No.

2510
05:20:52,120 --> 05:21:00,140
[SPEAKER_16] You taught the exact opposite to the country and to the wider world.

2511
05:21:01,120 --> 05:21:08,660
[SPEAKER_16] That the most wicked can be defeated by the most ordinary flesh-and-blood people.

2512
05:21:08,780 --> 05:21:14,840
[SPEAKER_16] That against the machinery of power, another machinery of power is not needed.

2513
05:21:15,120 --> 05:21:34,620
[SPEAKER_16] But rather flesh-and-blood people, who are capable of anything from mailbox to mailbox, house to house, in winter, in frost, in rain, for their country, for their neighbors, for their relatives, for their community.

2514
05:21:34,980 --> 05:21:38,260
[SPEAKER_16] There is no greater power than this.

2515
05:21:38,320 --> 05:21:45,100
[SPEAKER_16] History will teach in books that light defeats darkness.

2516
05:21:45,120 --> 05:21:50,540
[SPEAKER_16] The story, the decency, defeats evil.

2517
05:22:02,120 --> 05:22:14,440
[UNKNOWN] Dear friends, you, tens, hundreds of thousands of you, have shown the kinder, more humane face of Hungary.

2518
05:22:15,120 --> 05:22:17,600
[SPEAKER_16] This is the Hungary that wants to act.

2519
05:22:17,760 --> 05:22:22,080
[SPEAKER_16] This is the Hungary that is cheerful and joyful.

2520
05:22:22,200 --> 05:22:26,460
[SPEAKER_16] This is the Hungary that knows no impossibilities.

2521
05:22:27,680 --> 05:22:29,740
[SPEAKER_16] Honored fellow citizens!

2522
05:22:31,120 --> 05:22:33,940
[UNKNOWN] [UNKNOWN] This is your day of celebration.

2523
05:22:34,860 --> 05:22:43,860
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] We wish to express our gratitude for what we have received from the Hungarian people in the past years, months, and weeks.

2524
05:22:43,860 --> 05:22:46,640
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] For walking with us on the road.

2525
05:22:47,860 --> 05:22:50,880
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] For lifting us up when we fell.

2526
05:22:51,040 --> 05:22:55,520
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] For believing in us even when no one else did.

2527
05:22:55,760 --> 05:23:08,620
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] For giving this wonderful country the chance to be a happy, free, functioning, and once again humane home.

2528
05:23:09,460 --> 05:23:13,340
[UNKNOWN] [UNKNOWN] I swear to you, always

2529
05:23:13,340 --> 05:23:16,180
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] we will always remember this.

2530
05:23:17,340 --> 05:23:26,480
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] We will always remember the strength of the freedom-loving, patriotic Hungarian people who brought about change.

2531
05:23:27,340 --> 05:23:32,680
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Today, we embrace one another, we take each other's hands.

2532
05:23:33,000 --> 05:23:42,660
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] We thank one another, strangers and familiar faces alike, for being able to stand here in this wonderful country.

2533
05:23:42,660 --> 05:23:44,880
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] In this wonderful city.

2534
05:23:44,960 --> 05:23:46,900
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] On this wonderful square.

2535
05:23:47,040 --> 05:23:50,440
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] In front of the most wonderful building in the world.

2536
05:23:50,560 --> 05:23:51,420
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] Thank you!

2537
05:24:05,740 --> 05:24:06,740
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] My friends!

2538
05:24:07,400 --> 05:24:09,900
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] In the past two years

2539
05:24:09,900 --> 05:24:15,400
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] I have visited more than 700 settlements in Hungary.

2540
05:24:15,860 --> 05:24:18,900
[SPEAKER_16] [SPEAKER_16] I have met countless people.

2541
05:24:19,540 --> 05:24:24,340
[SPEAKER_16] I do not have the opportunity to thank each and every one of you individually.

2542
05:24:24,580 --> 05:24:38,900
[SPEAKER_16] Therefore, from here, I send my message to everyone who shook my hand, asked me a question, took a photo with me, hugged me, or prayed with me.

2543
05:24:39,900 --> 05:24:49,960
[SPEAKER_16] I encourage you, never, never to forget what you have taught me about Hungary.

2544
05:24:50,640 --> 05:24:58,580
[SPEAKER_16] In Tarnasadány, Komló, Püspökladány, Ózd, Gyula, and throughout the country.

2545
05:24:58,900 --> 05:25:04,920
[SPEAKER_16] What I have received and learned from you, I will carry with me for a lifetime.

2546
05:25:05,100 --> 05:25:08,900
[SPEAKER_16] You have not only changed the country, but me as well.

2547
05:25:09,900 --> 05:25:11,000
[SPEAKER_16] Thank you.

2548
05:25:26,900 --> 05:25:38,720
[SPEAKER_16] I have learned from you that one of the most important tasks in the coming years will be to learn once again to see ourselves as a community.

2549
05:25:39,900 --> 05:25:54,520
[SPEAKER_16] Therefore, I ask you to turn to those fellow citizens of ours who are disappointed today, who are afraid, who experience this period as a loss.

2550
05:25:54,700 --> 05:26:00,920
[SPEAKER_16] Do not try to defeat them, do not try to humiliate them.

2551
05:26:02,120 --> 05:26:06,100
[UNKNOWN] Listen to them, speak with them.

2552
05:26:06,780 --> 05:26:08,500
[SPEAKER_16] Tell them,

2553
05:26:08,500 --> 05:26:12,600
[SPEAKER_16] that this country is theirs as well, because it belongs to everyone.

2554
05:26:13,500 --> 05:26:17,980
[UNKNOWN] That they are also needed, because everyone is needed.

2555
05:26:18,180 --> 05:26:23,580
[SPEAKER_16] And that together, together we will rebuild Hungary.

2556
05:26:23,780 --> 05:26:28,800
[SPEAKER_16] Because there is no right, no left, only Hungarian.

2557
05:26:39,180 --> 05:26:56,920
[SPEAKER_16] And I ask you, I ask you to also turn to those who are in need, who are lonely, who have lost their faith, who feel that no one sees them anymore.

2558
05:26:57,240 --> 05:27:05,700
[SPEAKER_16] Because the true strength of a country is not measured by the number of parliamentary mandates the winners hold,

2559
05:27:05,700 --> 05:27:11,980
[UNKNOWN] but by how we treat the most vulnerable people.

2560
05:27:12,700 --> 05:27:16,200
[SPEAKER_16] And you know this better than anyone.

2561
05:27:28,700 --> 05:27:33,020
[UNKNOWN] Many congratulate, but you know them well.

2562
05:27:33,020 --> 05:27:36,720
[SPEAKER_16] The real work is just beginning now.

2563
05:27:38,020 --> 05:27:45,260
[SPEAKER_16] Now is the time to build communities, to talk, to debate, to help one another.

2564
05:27:46,020 --> 05:28:00,100
[SPEAKER_16] And to learn anew, and to show each other that politics can be decent, human, brave, honest, beautiful, and useful.

2565
05:28:00,700 --> 05:28:03,000
[UNKNOWN] If it cannot be now, then it cannot be.

2566
05:28:03,020 --> 05:28:09,640
[UNKNOWN] But if you are renewed and go home, then politics will be left alone again.

2567
05:28:11,020 --> 05:28:16,280
[SPEAKER_16] For without you, we do not want to, and we will not govern.

2568
05:28:16,800 --> 05:28:23,660
[SPEAKER_16] Dear fellow citizens, we will represent every Hungarian, but you must do it as well.

2569
05:28:33,020 --> 05:28:50,280
[UNKNOWN] I ask you to continue to establish islands, to organize local communities, to get to know each other, to be curious about one another, and to be curious about Hungary.

2570
05:28:54,100 --> 05:29:02,240
[SPEAKER_16] We would like to request a medical team for the organizing balloon; people are waving at the Rákóczi statue.

2571
05:29:02,240 --> 05:29:06,040
[SPEAKER_16] I ask the organizers to send medical personnel there.

2572
05:29:12,240 --> 05:29:24,420
[SPEAKER_16] Be curious about one another, and be curious about Hungary, because this country is full of wonders, full of fantastic people.

2573
05:29:24,820 --> 05:29:31,240
[SPEAKER_16] This wonderful country is not the country of hatred, not the country of fear.

2574
05:29:32,240 --> 05:29:34,620
[SPEAKER_16] Not the country of hopelessness.

2575
05:29:34,740 --> 05:29:42,360
[SPEAKER_16] Hungary is the homeland of talented, free, brave, and decent people.

2576
05:29:44,920 --> 05:29:45,980
[UNKNOWN] Hungary is the homeland of talented, free, brave, and decent people.

2577
05:29:45,980 --> 05:29:53,120
[UNKNOWN] Hungary is the homeland of talented, free, brave, and decent people.

2578
05:29:53,300 --> 05:29:54,360
[UNKNOWN] Hungary is the homeland of talented, free, brave, and decent people.

2579
05:29:55,160 --> 05:30:05,820
[SPEAKER_16] Fellow citizens, Hungarians! I would like to ask you to preserve something from this day for everyone.

2580
05:30:07,060 --> 05:30:11,540
[SPEAKER_16] Keep this joy, this openness!

2581
05:30:12,360 --> 05:30:13,780
[SPEAKER_16] This love!

2582
05:30:13,980 --> 05:30:20,500
[SPEAKER_16] Because in the years ahead, Hungary will need this the most.

2583
05:30:22,160 --> 05:30:27,500
[SPEAKER_16] Take it with you! Take this day with you as a memory!

2584
05:30:28,960 --> 05:30:33,240
[SPEAKER_16] Remember this day for the rest of your lives!

2585
05:30:34,580 --> 05:30:39,100
[SPEAKER_16] Remember what Hungary looked like today!

2586
05:30:39,980 --> 05:30:41,900
[SPEAKER_16] It may be that one day,

2587
05:30:42,360 --> 05:30:46,360
[SPEAKER_16] you will show it to your children, your grandchildren,

2588
05:30:46,960 --> 05:30:56,660
[SPEAKER_16] and tell them this was the first day of a free, democratic Hungary in 2026.

2589
05:31:05,360 --> 05:31:10,280
[SPEAKER_16] We would like to introduce a little girl who has lost her parents.

2590
05:31:10,360 --> 05:31:11,700
[SPEAKER_16] Come up here for a moment!

2591
05:31:13,660 --> 05:31:14,820
[SPEAKER_16] Please help her!

2592
05:31:15,120 --> 05:31:15,640
[SPEAKER_16] Do you have her?

2593
05:31:17,760 --> 05:31:19,520
[SPEAKER_16] There is a little girl here, what is her name?

2594
05:31:21,480 --> 05:31:23,340
[SPEAKER_16] There she is, excuse me!

2595
05:31:24,980 --> 05:31:29,620
[SPEAKER_16] There, to my left, a lady is raising her hand, there a child has been lost...

2596
05:31:30,360 --> 05:31:33,660
[SPEAKER_16] There is a child here, so if anyone is looking for their child, please come over.

2597
05:31:37,060 --> 05:31:42,140
[UNKNOWN] So, what I ask of you is to take this day with you as a memory!

2598
05:31:42,360 --> 05:31:48,140
[SPEAKER_16] And once again, please allow us to thank you!

2599
05:31:49,360 --> 05:31:55,600
[SPEAKER_16] We thank you for your trust, for that completely overwhelming amount of work,

2600
05:31:56,360 --> 05:32:02,120
[UNKNOWN] we thank you for the prayers, the kindness, and the encouragement,

2601
05:32:02,280 --> 05:32:08,580
[SPEAKER_16] And we thank you for all those many, many kind words and love that we have received.

2602
05:32:09,360 --> 05:32:11,140
[SPEAKER_16] And I ask you,

2603
05:32:11,140 --> 05:32:15,440
[SPEAKER_16] on behalf of every Hungarian, to celebrate now!

2604
05:32:16,140 --> 05:32:29,000
[UNKNOWN] I ask you to embrace one another, to sing, to laugh,

2605
05:32:29,000 --> 05:32:35,300
[SPEAKER_16] because a very, very long and often bumpy road has led us here,

2606
05:32:35,420 --> 05:32:41,080
[SPEAKER_16] but today we can finally rejoice, and there is something to rejoice about,

2607
05:32:41,140 --> 05:32:45,440
[SPEAKER_16] so let us rejoice, and finally let there be dancing!

2608
05:33:05,100 --> 05:33:06,260
[SPEAKER_16] Let it be!

2609
05:33:08,160 --> 05:33:11,040
[SPEAKER_16] Let me say goodbye,

2610
05:33:12,260 --> 05:33:20,980
[UNKNOWN] and I wish everyone here a very good, peaceful, joyful time today,

2611
05:33:21,060 --> 05:33:23,220
[SPEAKER_16] and all across the country!

2612
05:33:23,960 --> 05:33:25,780
[SPEAKER_16] Thank you for being with us!

2613
05:33:26,280 --> 05:33:30,160
[SPEAKER_16] God bless free Hungary!

2614
